    <node id="After discovering that the four-cent stamps are the cause of the poisonings in a Tennessee community, Andy proposes several drastic measures to combat the threat. First, he suggests getting someone, possibly even the President, to make a public announcement on all radio and TV networks explaining the situation with the four-cent stamps and warning against licking any stamps. Before this announcement, he also proposes checking the security clearances at the plant where the stamps are printed, as it is possible that someone was planted there years ago for this operation. Although there is no evidence yet that it was a plot, he suggests investigating who had access to the stickum used in the stamps, as it could have been an accident caused by a chemical in the stickum. He also proposes releasing propaganda about the United States &quot;whipping&quot; the mystery virus and sending a stamp collection to the Kremlin. Tired from the investigation, Andy ultimately defers to his superior to take action." />
