    <node id="1. Continue Investigating the Crisis: Sergeant Andy plans to continue investigating the situation with high priority and cooperation from the officers. He will leverage his expertise and that of his staff to figure out the cause of the crisis.&#10;&#10;2. Public Announcement: Andy suggests having someone, possibly even the President, make a public announcement on all radio and TV networks explaining the situation and warning against any potential dangers. This measure aims to ensure the safety of the public and prevent further harm.&#10;&#10;3. Investigating the Source: Sergeant Andy proposes checking security clearances at the plant where the stamps are printed and investigating who had access to the stickum used in the stamps. This step is aimed at identifying if there was any malicious intent or an accident caused by a chemical in the stickum.&#10;&#10;4. Propaganda: He also plans to release propaganda about the United States &quot;whipping&quot; the mystery virus, which could help maintain public morale and confidence during this critical situation.&#10;&#10;5. International Gesture: Sending a stamp collection to the Kremlin is another step Sergeant Andy proposes, which could serve as an international gesture and potentially help in resolving the crisis or gaining support from other nations.&#10;&#10;In summary, Sergeant Andy plans to take several steps to address the critical situation with top priority and cooperation from the officers. These measures include making a public announcement, investigating the source of the problem, releasing propaganda, and making an international gesture." />
