    <node id="The outcome of Andy's frantic efforts on the phone was that he gathered information from worried doctors, hospital administrators, and nurses about a mysterious epidemic that was sweeping the country. He compiled this information into charts and graphs to help identify potential trends or causes of the epidemic.&#10;&#10;When the chicken colonel, who reminded Andy of General Rommel, entered the office with two young officers, Andy initially found it amusing and had to suppress a laugh. However, he quickly became serious when the colonel informed him that a noncom was supposed to be in charge of the office but hadn't shown up yet.&#10;&#10;Andy, who had been &quot;entombed&quot; in the office for several days, was exasperated by the situation and snapped at a flustered brigadier general. He then learned that Janis, one of his co-workers, had written a letter to her mother about their work, potentially putting their efforts at risk.&#10;&#10;The colonel, who was initially confused about why a noncom was in charge, quickly realized the gravity of the situation when Andy showed him the headline of a newspaper that read &quot;RED PLAGUE SWEEPS NATION.&quot; The colonel and his captains were then stationed by the switchboard and ordered to take orders only from Andy and Bettijean." />
